title: 820-00840 20v not booting
message:
Board came in turning on sometimes with some water damage near U8400 and U7650 after UC I get 20v but no more power, I have tried do reflow all chips near the water damage area, but no luck.

PPBUS_G3H 13v
PP3V3_G3H 3.3v
PP5V_S5 5v
PP5V_S4 0v
PP3V3_S4 0v

title: 820-00840 20v not booting
message:
Some small resistors or traces affected by corrosion.
UC can easy break traces already affected by corrosion; when no sweep option is used.
Also inspect for knocked off components.

Do you get 3V3_S5 at least?
Trigger SMC_ONOFF_L and check for drop pulse at PM_PWRBTN_L ay same time.

title: 820-00840 20v not booting
message:
3V3_S5 was present, funny thing is that now that more than a full day has gone by the board starts up just fine, maybe some residue from the UC was causing a problem.

Thanks!
